400 g Turkey Breast Steak
250 g Microwaveable Rice
1 cup Tikka Sauce
125 g Roasted Peppers
7 g Cilantro
2 unit(s) Flatbread
4 tbsp Garlic Spread
9 g Indian Spice Mix
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Oil*
½ cup Milk*

Before starting, preheat the broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce.
Pat turkey dry with paper towels, then cut into 1-inch pieces.
Roughly chop cilantro.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high. When hot add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then turkey.
Cook for 3-4 min, stirring often, until turkey is golden.
Add Indian Spice Mix. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until turkey is coated. Season with salt and pepper.

To the same pan, add tikka sauce, roasted peppers with their liquid and 1/2 cup (1 cup) milk.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Cook for 4-5 min, stirring often, until turkey is cooked through and sauce has thickened slightly.**
Add half the cilantro. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Follow the package directions for microwaving rice.

Meanwhile, on an unlined baking sheet, arrange flatbreads, then brush with garlic spread.
Broil in the middle of the oven for 3 min, until golden. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!)

Cut flatbreads into quarters.
Divide rice between plates then top with turkey tikka.
Sprinkle remaining cilantro over top.
Serve garlic flatbreads alongside.